  <object name="LetThereBeLight">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <alias>Courtyard</alias>
    <description><![CDATA[<br/>You've crossed the skeleton and are in a smalll courtyard. <br/><br/>To your left is a thrift store. Years of sunlight and weather have bleached the letters and worn them down to near-nothing, requiring you to afford more than a glance to read them. It says, "esmond's Pawn Shop". The first letter is missing. Probably a "D". <br/><br/>Straight ahead against a building wall, are solar panels and a generator, sitting under a short metal roof. <br/><br/>The only way to continue appears to be via a large iron bulkhead door in the building to the right. The building appears to be some sort of makeshift military complex.]]></description>
    <object name="solarpanels">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <movepanelsintosun>I can't do that. They are firmly bolted into the cement.</movepanelsintosun>
      <cleaned type="boolean">false</cleaned>
      <smashed type="boolean">false</smashed>
      <alias>solar panels</alias>
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <look type="script">
        if (solarpanels.cleaned = False) {
          msg ("It's an array of solar panels bolted into the cement ground. The panels are covered in dirt and grime. Wires snake from the panels to a nearby generator.")
        }
        else if (solarpanels.cleaned = True) {
          msg ("The solar panels are moderately clean now that I wiped them off. But they still aren't going anywhere since they are bolted to the ground. And trying to use brute force would never work; they are too fragile.")
        }
      </look>
      <cleanpanels type="script">
        msg ("You wipe the panels off in a delicate, but determined manner. It's not back to factory-new conditions, but its better than nothing. The question is how do you get light to reach them, with the metal roof casting a shadow.")
        solarpanels.cleaned = True
      </cleanpanels>
      <useon type="scriptdictionary">
        <item key="CellPhone"><![CDATA[
          msg ("<br/>You attempt to scan the solar panel with your cell phone. <br/><br/>The reprogrammed device alerts you that there are no computer chips of any kind to interface with in the solar panel array.")
        ]]></item>
        <item key="MysteriousOrb"><![CDATA[
          msg ("<br/>You pull out the mysterious orb and move it closer to the solar panels; finally touching one.<br/><br/>The mysterious orb continues being mysterious, as it has no reaction to the solar panel; and vice versa.")
        ]]></item>
        <item key="Metalpole"><![CDATA[
          if (solarpanels.smashed = False) {
            msg ("You bring your metal pole to bear, and strike a solar panel with a thwack.<br/><br/>The panel shatters, but the bolts in the base keep the structure upright.<br/><br/>You ask yourself, \"Why'd I do that?\" and you reply to yourself, \"for funsies.\"<br/><br/>Although, you resolve to not do it again, as having some intact solar panels is vital to powering that generator.")
            solarpanels.smashed = True
          }
          else if (solarpanels.smashed = True) {
            msg ("You promised yourself that you wouldn't go Gallagher on any more solar panels. They are the only thing that can power that generator; which will allow you to open the large iron door.")
          }
        ]]></item>
        <item key="mirror"><![CDATA[
          msg ("You turn the mirror so that the sun reflects off of it, directing the rays onto a solar panel.")
          if (solarpanels.cleaned = True) {
            msg ("<br/>A light on the generator begins blinking yellow, before turning to a solid green. The generator seems to be powering up correctly. <br/><br/>However, the iron door is not reacting to the generator as it powers up.<br/><br/>Ziggy offers to hold the mirror in place, while you inspect the generator and iron door.")
            generator.charged = True
          }
          else {
            msg ("<br/>A light on the nearby generator blinks red. Something is happening, but not enough light is being absorbed by the solar panels.")
          }
