      <turnon type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (survivorrecording.fixed = True) {
          msg ("A message plays, <br/><br/>\"Sergeant Mason Jin, here. I got caught behind in the lockdown. The facility was overrun in a matter of seconds. I saw Wyle, Chavez, Martin, and Raz all die. The Metas came in through the roof, and poured down on top of us. Damn they're still smart. Command was wrong. <br/><br/>In the chaos, something big tore a hole down through the bunker via the auditorium. That got me down here to the reactor. I put on a suit, but that'll be useful til' I need to take a wiz - or eat. I see the creatures through the window. They're in the observation deck. I hope that glass holds them.<br/><br/><i> sigh </i><br/><br/>I'm afraid... because I know there's no way out. They probably can't get to me here, but... here is where'll I'll stay. <br/><br/>This is all thanks to Ashland Nanotech. I hope the weight of 7 billion lives bears down on their conscious' til' the moment they die. <i>(The man breaths heavily for a few moments, before continuing)</i><br/><br/>It's tough... because you can't fight these things like a human. You don't engage The Metas, worried that you'll die. You worry that you'll survive. Because if you do, you might live long enough to become one.<br/><br/>But... <i>(There is a long silence) </i> I won't let that happen. <i> You hear the sound of a gun cocking in the audio recording </i>\"<br/><br/>The recording stops there.")
        }
        else {
          msg ("<br/>You can't hear a word. <br/><br/>The diagnostics mentioned an audio error in this robot. An error message on the control console flashes, saying, \"Audio couplings inoperable.\" <br/><br/>Maybe there's a way to fix it.")
        }
      ]]></turnon>
      <alias>recording</alias>
    </object>
    <object name="TextOnWalls">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look><![CDATA[There are various words scribbled on the wall in this room. <br/><br/>"They've won. A war of attrition. And they won." <br/><br/>"Metamorphs!" <br/><br/>"They can't take you if you're dead." <br/><br/>"Death is the only way out." <br/><br/>"Burn in hell Ashland Nanotech." ]]></look>
      <alias>message scribbled on wall</alias>
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <object name="RadiationSuitBody">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>body in radiation suit</alias>
      <look><![CDATA[The body is perfectly preserved, other than its total dessication. Essentially, it is a mummy. <br/><br/>There's a hole on both sides of the temple of the radiation suit's mask. A gun still rests, firmly grasped in the right hand.]]></look>
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <object name="coreroomgun">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look>That pistol appears like new.</look>
      <visible type="boolean">false</visible>
      <scenery />
      <takemsg>That pistol is highly radioactive. Also, this MARS robot does not have an inventory.</takemsg>
    </object>
  </object>
  <object name="ReactorCoreRoom">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <description type="script"><![CDATA[
      ClearScreen
      msg ("<br/>This is it... the Reactor Control Room. Resetting the reactor would reset security overrides, and open the bunker doors.<br/><br/>The energy leaking from the core is almost blinding; even viewing it through a small camera on the MARS.")
    ]]></description>
    <alias>Reactor Core Room</alias>
    <object name="ReactorCoreActual">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>Reactor Core</alias>
      <look>It's the reactor. The core is obviously functioning at a high capacity. This must be where all power is originating; even for the bed of live wires around that massive skeleton.</look>
      <attemptreset type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("<br/>This puzzle is not currently working. You have reached the end of the demo. Thanks for playing!<br/>")
        picture ("Rod Alignment 1.PNG")
      ]]></attemptreset>
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <exit alias="west" to="CorePrepRoom">
      <inherit name="westdirection" />
    </exit>
  </object>
